The `ultralytics/models/sam/modules/utils.py` file generally contains various utility functions that support the core functionalities of the SAM (Segment Anything Model) module. These functions, such as `select_closest_cond_frames` and `get_1d_sine_pe`, are likely designed to perform specific helper tasks, data manipulations, or common computations that are leveraged by other components within the SAM architecture.
